sentences: Ernest Ray Lane (March 16, 1931 – July 8, 2012) was an American blues pianist.
He played various blues musicians and bands, including with Pinetop Perkins, Robert Nighthawk, Ike Turner, George "Harmonica" Smith, and Canned Heat.
